{"id":12393,"date":"2022-03-15T17:59:17","date_gmt":"2022-03-15T10:59:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/?p=12393"},"modified":"2022-04-21T13:36:49","modified_gmt":"2022-04-21T06:36:49","slug":"how-a-traditional-engagement-is-held-in-vietnam","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/how-a-traditional-engagement-is-held-in-vietnam\/","title":{"rendered":"How A Traditional Engagement Is Held In Vietnam"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-c264e89\" data-block-id=\"c264e89\"><style>.stk-c264e89{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-c264e89{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-c264e89{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-c264e89-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-04cccbf\" data-block-id=\"04cccbf\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-04cccbf-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-04cccbf-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Ask for the bride Ceremony ( L\u1ec5 \u0103n h\u1ecfi) is traditional ceremony which could be considered&nbsp;a betrothal in Vietnam that should be hold before the wedding.&nbsp;Have been maintained constantly over hundreds of years, the ceremony is a must stage in every traditional wedding in Vietnam<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Both families will choose a good day to hold this ceremony at the bride\u2019s house.The time is chosen very carefully based on the propitious time and day of lunar calendar. Each family, then, chooses a representative. This person is a member of the family which has a happy life and a high ranking position in the family. They will prepare a speech to talk infront of two families.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/CB9_9111.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12399\"><figcaption><em>Unmarried mans and womans\u00a0are chosen to be the tray beholders<\/em><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-b264482\" data-block-id=\"b264482\"><style>.stk-b264482{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-b264482{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-b264482{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-b264482-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-dc974d9\" data-block-id=\"dc974d9\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-dc974d9-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-dc974d9-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Before coming to the bride\u2019s house on the betrothal day, the groom\u2019s family will prepare gifts. Traditionally the gifts was placed a number of trays. The number must be an odd number 5, 7 or 9\u2026 trays depends on the condition of the fianc\u00e9 family. The tray will be covered with red silk.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Vietnamese believe that the red color and the odd numbers are sign of luck which is important for a happy wedding. Depending on the number of trays, each family will choose 5, 7 or 9 young and married boys and girls&nbsp;to bring and receive the gifts.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/CB9_9138.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12401\"><figcaption><em>Young and unmarried boys and girls bring and receive the gifts<\/em><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"681\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/CB9_9142.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12403\"><figcaption><em>The groom\u2019s family will be greeted warmly by the family of the bride.<\/em><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-9986b82\" data-block-id=\"9986b82\"><style>.stk-9986b82{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-9986b82{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-9986b82{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-9986b82-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-fdcb23d\" data-block-id=\"fdcb23d\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-fdcb23d-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-fdcb23d-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">On the&nbsp;Vietnamese engagement day, the groom\u2019s family along with these young people will bring the gifts to the bride\u2019s house. They will be received a warm welcome from the bride\u2019s family.&nbsp;On this day. the house of the bride will be decorated beautifully. Still, red is one of the main color that is chosen in the decoration for the day.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">After receiving the gifts, the young couple prays in front of the fianc\u00e9e\u2019s family altar to ask for approval of fianc\u00e9e ancestors. When this ritual finishes, the couple are officially known as fiance\u00e9 and fianc\u00e9.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1154\" height=\"768\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/FZN_1658.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12411\"><figcaption><em>Decoration at the bride\u2019s house planned by The Planners<\/em><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1154\" height=\"768\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/FZN_2078.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12413\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1154\" height=\"768\" data-id=\"12415\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/FZN_2118.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12415\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1154\" height=\"768\" data-id=\"12419\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/FZN_2154.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12419\"><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1154\" height=\"768\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/FZN_2166.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12423\"><figcaption><em>The engagement day is alo a chance for two families to sit down and get to know each other better before the wedding day<\/em><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-2 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"1154\" data-id=\"12405\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/CB9_9257.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12405\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1154\" height=\"768\" data-id=\"12409\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/CB9_9262.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-12409\"><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-3 is-layout-fle